      <item>
        <title>Extrepo doesn&#39;t include Trixie</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[arraybolt3]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Debian Salsa is Debian’s official Git forge, and it is a Gitlab instance. While I don’t know for certain if <em>that specific</em> extrepo repository is the official one upstream, I wouldn’t be surprised if it was, and extrepo is part of Debian. Our documentation recommends using it in some areas, so it would be good if it were kept up-to-date. I may be able to get the time to submit a fix upstream to re-enable the Trixie repo now that we have one.</p>
